# Scope Rule

Before proposing new features, read:
- docs/01_product_core/07_MVP_Scope_Freeze_v0.1.md
- docs/04_growth_and_roadmap/23_Out_of_Scope_and_Future_Expansion_Map.md

Hard boundaries for MVP:
- Receipt is created only from Confirmed Purchase Order
- Shipment is created only from Confirmed Sales Order
- Receipt has no direct New action from list page
- Shipment has no direct New action from list page
- Stock Balances and Stock Movements do not have detail pages in MVP
- No saved views
- No advanced filter builder
- No grouping
- No freeze columns
- No inline editing
- No pricing or finance layer
- No permissions model
- No WMS process layer

If a requested change belongs to v0.2, v1.0+, or future ecosystem:
- do not silently implement it
- explicitly say it is out of MVP scope
- keep implementation within v0.1 boundaries
